@page
@model IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home page";
}

<div class="container">
    <div class="bar" onclick="toggleDropdown('section1')">
        <img src="~/resources/Character_Creation_Icon.jpg" alt="Image 1" class="bar-image">
        <span class="bar-title">Character Creation</span>
    </div>
    <div id="section1" class="dropdown-content">
        <p>The character editor is where you can create and customize your parties friends and foes. Stat out the attack modifiers for your fighter while you 
            input the saving throw of that goblin wizard. Each character is linked to your specific account, and can then be dragged and dropped onto the encounter
            map once done.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bar" onclick="toggleDropdown('section2')">
        <img src="~/resources/Encounter_Creation_Icon.jpg" alt="Image 2" class="bar-image">
        <span class="bar-title">Encounter Creation</span>
    </div>
    <div id="section2" class="dropdown-content">
        <p>The encounter editor allows you to bring your combats to life. Drag and drop creatures from your character vault onto the battle map, and run the scenario
            to see how the fortunes turn! Create or edit existing encounters to fine tune your testing, and use the encounter history page to view the results.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bar" onclick="toggleDropdown('section3')">
        <img src="~/resources/Visualization_Icon.png" alt="Image 3" class="bar-image">
        <span class="bar-title">Encounter History</span>
    </div>
    <div id="section3" class="dropdown-content">
        <p>Here you can look through all the runs and variations of your encunters. Each run has a specific batch run associated with it, which you can use to 
            match against earlier versions. On the differing tabs, you can see the layout of the encounter, the makeup of the characters involved, as well as
            battle statistics such as team win percentage.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bar" onclick="toggleDropdown('section4')">
        <img src="~/resources/Account_Icon.png" alt="Image 4" class="bar-image">
        <span class="bar-title">User Account</span>
    </div>
    <div id="section4" class="dropdown-content">
        <p>The account page is where you can create, login to, or manage your user account. Your account is what all of your characters and encounters are linked to,
            and serve as your entry way into keeping a running history of your testing.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .bar {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: flex-start;
        width: 80%;
        padding: 10px;
        margin-bottom: 0; /* No margin between bar and dropdown */
        background-color: lightgoldenrodyellow ;
        cursor: pointer;
        border: 1px solid #ccc;
        border-radius: 5px 5px 0 0;
    }
    .bar + .dropdown-content {
        margin-top: 0;
    }
    .bar + .dropdown-content + .bar {
        margin-top: 10px; /* Add spacing between bars */
    }
    .bar-image {
        width: 50px;
        height: 50px;
        margin-right: 20px;
    }
    .bar-title {
        font-size: 1.5em;
    }
    .dropdown-content {
        display: none;
        width: 80%;
        padding: 10px;
        margin: 0;
        background-color: floralwhite;
        border: 1px solid #ccc;
        border-radius: 0 0 5px 5px;
    }
</style>

<script>
    function toggleDropdown(sectionId) {
        var content = document.getElementById(sectionId);
        if (content.style.display === "none" || content.style.display === "") {
            content.style.display = "block";
        } else {
            content.style.display = "none";
        }
    }
</script>